# Hosted Checkout Monitoring — agent context

Before planning or implementing changes in this repo, **read [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)** for system features, code structure, architecture, and edit conventions.

## Quick reference

- **Stack:** Python 3.13, FastAPI, Jinja2/HTMX, PostgreSQL, optional read-only MariaDB enrichment
- **Production:** RHEL 9 + rootless Podman Compose — see `deploy/rhel9/README.md`
- **Shared scenario engine:** `scenarios.py`, `io_utils.py`, `wallet_enrichment.py` (web + desktop `run.py`)
- **Layers:** routers → services → models/DB; keep routers thin
- **Schema:** Alembic migrations in `alembic/versions/` — never hand-edit production DB
- **Roles:** `admin` (users only), `supervisor` (imports/scenarios/export), `investigator` (case work)
- **Security:** no secrets in repo; respect `ALLOWED_TRANSITIONS` and investigator policy; no outbound PII/AI APIs

## Where to edit (common tasks)

| Task | Start here |
|------|------------|
| New route/page | `app/routers/web.py` + `app/templates/` |
| Scenario logic | `scenarios.py`, then `app/services/scenario_run.py` |
| Imports / Excel | `io_utils.py`, `app/services/import_service.py` |
| Detection workflow | `app/constants.py`, `app/services/detections_service.py` |
| DB change | `app/models.py` + new Alembic revision |
| Config / env | `.env.example`, `app/config.py`, `app/startup_checks.py` |

When in doubt, follow patterns in neighboring files and keep diffs minimal.
